Who's that coming?

53
00:07:20.303 --> 00:07:21.846
It's Papa and Pete.

54
00:07:22.973 --> 00:07:24.307
Come on, Newt.

55
00:07:58.258 --> 00:08:02.512
Can't get over that Booker Savage
kicking his kid out in a storm like that.


56
00:08:02.595 --> 00:08:07.017
That poor boy.
No mother, and a father like that.


57
00:08:07.100 --> 00:08:08.768
It's awful.

58
00:08:08.852 --> 00:08:10.770
Come and sit at the table, Rob.

59
00:08:12.313 --> 00:08:14.315
You can help, Newt.

60
00:08:15.191 --> 00:08:18.028
| still give the orders around here,
Miss Prissy.


61
00:08:19.529 --> 00:08:22.615
Newt's going straight to bed after supper.
Church tomorrow.


62
00:08:23.283 --> 00:08:25.577
This town must really be messed up now.

63
00:08:25.660 --> 00:08:30.373
[Jack] Place is due for some punishing,
all the sinning going on around here.


64
00:08:30.457 --> 00:08:32.917
[Prissy] Newt, you can help me
with the dishes tonight.


65
00:08:33.001 --> 00:08:34.961
Prissy, that's enough.

66
00:08:42.302 --> 00:08:46.389
Bless us, O Lord,
for this food we are about to receive.


67
00:08:48.058 --> 00:08:52.896
And we thank thee, O Lord,
for saving us from the storm.


68
00:08:53.772 --> 00:08:56.524
[man] Lord, may the storm
you brought upon us


69
00:08:56.608 --> 00:08:58.943
leave us repentant.

70
00:08:59.027 --> 00:09:03.239
Let those of us who survive
give thanks to your goodness.


71
00:09:03.948 --> 00:09:07.660
Soften the hearts of those who oppress us.

72
00:09:08.328 --> 00:09:13.666
Spare us the violence and hatred
that visits our daily lives.


73
00:09:14.667 --> 00:09:17.420
Deliver our young from cigarettes,

74
00:09:18.171 --> 00:09:21.382
from dancing, from drinking,

75
00:09:21.466 --> 00:09:24.636
from lipstick and flapper skirts.

76
00:09:24.719 --> 00:09:28.264
Yes, Lord, deliver us from all evil.

77
00:09:29.140 --> 00:09:31.851
And finally, O Lord,

78
00:09:31.935 --> 00:09:36.856
help us to live our lives
as you would have us live them.


79
00:09:36.940 --> 00:09:41.361
This we ask in Jesus's name. Amen.

80
00:09:43.154 --> 00:09:45.156
Before the services end,

81
00:09:45.240 --> 00:09:48.159
I'd like the congregation
to meet the wonderful family


82
00:09:48.243 --> 00:09:51.162
that's come to us
from way up in Canada.

83
00:09:51.788 --> 00:09:56.876
Brother Jefferson, will you,
your wife and daughter please stand?


84
00:10:00.588 --> 00:10:03.049
Thank you. Be seated.

85
00:10:03.133 --> 00:10:06.636
This marks the end of our services.

86
00:10:06.719 --> 00:10:09.305
God be with you till we meet again.

87
