93
00:10:32.036 --> 00:10:34.289
Oh, so that's it.

94
00:10:36.958 --> 00:10:39.419
-Hey, Newt!
-Oh, hi, Jappy.


95
00:10:39.502 --> 00:10:40.587
Hiya.

96
00:10:41.588 --> 00:10:43.548
Heard about you and Big Mabel.

97
00:10:45.508 --> 00:10:47.302
Gettin' caught in the storm.

98
00:10:48.636 --> 00:10:50.388
What all did you hear?

99
00:10:51.389 --> 00:10:54.350
| hear you ain't got no cherry no more.
[laughing]


100
00:10:55.393 --> 00:10:57.979
-How'd it feel, Newt?
-How'd what feel?


101
00:10:59.022 --> 00:11:01.107
Aw, come on. I ain't gonna snitch.

102
00:11:02.734 --> 00:11:05.153
Look, I don't wanna talk about it.

103
00:11:05.236 --> 00:11:08.281
Oh, come on, Newt. 
Big Mabel got you, huh?

104
00:11:09.407 --> 00:11:10.909
How did it feel, Newt?

105
00:11:12.202 --> 00:11:14.120
Come on. I ain't gonna snitch.

106
00:11:15.914 --> 00:11:18.708
We was wrapped up
in a gunny sack together.


107
00:11:20.168 --> 00:11:21.211
Naked?

108
00:11:23.004 --> 00:11:24.088
Naked.

109
00:11:25.131 --> 00:11:27.258
Boy, oh, boy, oh, boy. What else?

110
00:11:28.718 --> 00:11:32.472
-You gonna do it again, Newt?
-Oh, shut up! I told you everything.


111
00:11:32.555 --> 00:11:35.058
[boy] Come on, fellas. 
Get the lead out.

112
00:11:35.141 --> 00:11:36.893
Aw, what's the hurry?

113
00:11:41.564 --> 00:11:42.941
Where you guys headed?

114
00:11:44.025 --> 00:11:47.445
-Where you going, Winger?
-I'm going swimming.


115
00:11:47.528 --> 00:11:51.282
Old man Kiner's apples are good and ripe,
and I'm for going there first.


116
00:11:51.366 --> 00:11:53.159
Anybody against me?

117
00:11:53.243 --> 00:11:55.954
-Feel like apples, Beansy?
-I could eat some, I guess.


118
00:11:56.996 --> 00:11:58.206
How about you, Jappy?

119
00:11:59.123 --> 00:12:01.793
-It's okay with me.
-Well, then, let's go.


120
00:12:10.218 --> 00:12:13.388
-Those boys are stealing our apples.
-Ho! Ho!


121
00:12:27.026 --> 00:12:29.195
Hey! There's old man Kiner!

122
00:12:44.794 --> 00:12:45.920
[grunts]

123
00:12:54.053 --> 00:12:55.388
[woman] Jake!

124
00:12:56.264 --> 00:12:57.432
Jake!

125
00:12:59.142 --> 00:13:02.145
Oh! You'll pay for this!

126
00:13:03.980 --> 00:13:06.816
That old buzzard pushed his luck too far.

127
00:13:09.527 --> 00:13:11.112
What do you think they'll do?

128
00:13:11.195 --> 00:13:13.239
Don't give a damn what they gonna do.

129
00:13:13.323 --> 00:13:15.742
You all saw him hit me
with that whip first.


130
00:13:16.784 --> 00:13:19.162
You didn't have to beat him like that
after he was down.


131
00:13:21.289 --> 00:13:23.791
Well, fellas, ain't that something?

132
00:13:23.875 --> 00:13:27.545
Winger's stickin' up
for the poor white trash, a peckerwood,


133
00:13:27.628 --> 00:13:29.505
over one of his own gang.

134
00:13:29.589 --> 00:13:31.341
Mr. Kiner ain't that bad.

135
00:13:31.424 --> 00:13:34.719
He gives us just as much work
as he does white folks.


136
00:13:34.802 --> 00:13:37.347
How about all that cornmeal
he gave Beansy's pa last winter?


137
00:13:37.430 --> 00:13:40.391
To hell with last winter. 
He hit me today.

138
00:13:40.475 --> 00:13:42.101
Wasn't we stealing his apples?

139
00:13:42.185 --> 00:13:46.314
Look, Winger, all I wanna know is,
you with us or not?


140
00:13:51.861 --> 00:13:53.571
I'm always with the fellas here.

141
00:14:02.747 --> 00:14:06.084
You don't like nothing I do, Winger.
Nothing. You're always against me.


142
00:14:06.167 --> 00:14:07.835
| don't know what you mean.

143
00:14:07.919 --> 00:14:11.172
Yeah, you know what I mean.
You know exactly what I mean.


144
00:14:11.255 --> 00:14:13.508
Just keep it up.
You'll see what I'm getting at.


145
00:14:13.591 --> 00:14:15.134
Just keep it up.

146
00:14:19.055 --> 00:14:21.349
[Jappy] Last one in is a chicken's rump!

147
00:14:22.642 --> 00:14:25.061
[chattering, exclaiming]

148
00:14:36.948 --> 00:14:38.533
<i>On!</i>

149
00:14:38.616 --> 00:14:41.619
[boys laughing]

150
00:14:42.787 --> 00:14:44.288
[Jappy] Come on, Marcus!

151
00:14:45.123 --> 00:14:46.958
[boys shouting]

152
00:14:47.875 --> 00:14:49.752
[yells]

153
00:14:54.966 --> 00:14:56.634
[laughing, chattering]

154
00:15:16.654 --> 00:15:18.531
[engine turns off]

155
00:15:23.161 --> 00:15:24.287
Where's Newt?

156
00:15:25.246 --> 00:15:27.415
Swimmin' at the river, I 'spect.

157
00:15:27.498 --> 00:15:30.918
-You "'spect"? You don't know for sure?
-Yes?


158
00:15:32.211 --> 00:15:34.297
What is it?

159
00:15:34.380 --> 00:15:36.507
I'm hunting Newt and that gang of his.

160
00:15:36.591 --> 00:15:39.385
They stole Jake Kiner's apples
and beat up on him.


161
00:15:39.469 --> 00:15:42.472
Newt might have stole apples,
but he sure didn't hit Jake Kiner.


162
00:15:42.555 --> 00:15:44.223
Well, Mary Kiner says different.

163
00:15:44.307 --> 00:15:46.517
And Jake is damn near dead
in the hospital!


164
00:15:46.601 --> 00:15:48.603
You watch your tongue, Kirky.

165
00:15:53.232 --> 00:15:55.234
Run and get your papa from the barn.

166
00:15:57.069 --> 00:15:58.404
[engine starts]

167
00:15:58.488 --> 00:16:00.781
-[boys chuckling]
-[boy] The water was fine today.


168
00:16:00.865 --> 00:16:02.575
-[boy 2] Boy, oh, boy.
-[boy 3] Yeah.


169
00:16:02.658 --> 00:16:04.410
Wonder what Marcus is doing?

170
00:16:04.494 --> 00:16:07.246
[boy 2] I don't know.
He's a sorehead anyway.


171
00:16:07.330 --> 00:16:09.290
[boys chuckling]

172
00:16:11.000 --> 00:16:12.752
[boy 2] You wanna go in again?

173
00:16:17.840 --> 00:16:20.718
-[man] Roll again!
-That Marcus cut my pants off.


174
00:16:20.801 --> 00:16:23.012
Look what he did.
Did the same thing to mine.


175
00:16:23.095 --> 00:16:24.805
-[chuckles]
-Come on, Silas.


176
00:16:24.889 --> 00:16:27.225
-Here it is, Tuck.
-We gon' get drunk —


177
00:16:27.308 --> 00:16:28.851
-Oh!
-Good one.


178
00:16:28.935 --> 00:16:30.186
All yours.

179
00:16:31.020 --> 00:16:32.271
Fifty. I got you.

180
00:16:33.105 --> 00:16:36.400
Boy, they sure are having a good old time
at that crap game.


181
00:16:41.405 --> 00:16:42.740
[engine off]

182
00:16:52.458 --> 00:16:54.126
[men chattering]

183
00:16:54.210 --> 00:16:57.547
[Silas] Eight a-rollin'. A beautiful,
gallopin' horse. Come on, dice!


184
00:16:57.630 --> 00:17:00.007
[chattering continues]

185
00:17:03.177 --> 00:17:05.263
-Come on, Tuck!
-Everybody down. Let's go.


186
00:17:05.346 --> 00:17:06.472
Knock 'em back.

187
00:17:06.556 --> 00:17:10.017
[men chattering, exclaiming]

188
00:17:10.768 --> 00:17:12.353
Hey, there's Kirky.

189
00:17:14.272 --> 00:17:17.275
[men continue chattering]

190
00:17:21.070 --> 00:17:24.115
Tuck! Tuck! Kirky's coming!

191
00:17:30.121 --> 00:17:31.747
[Newt] Run, Tuck! Run!

192
00:17:36.294 --> 00:17:37.795
[boys whimpering]

193
00:17:39.880 --> 00:17:42.174
-[Kirky] Stop, damn it, or I'll shoot!
-[gunshot]


194
00:18:05.239 --> 00:18:07.325
You didn't have to shoot Tuck.

195
00:18:08.951 --> 00:18:11.787
Well, now you can see
what happens to criminals,


196
00:18:11.871 --> 00:18:14.498
especially the kind that goes around
beatin' up on white folks


197
00:18:14.582 --> 00:18:16.042
and running from the law.

198
00:18:17.043 --> 00:18:18.961
Tuck didn't beat up nobody.

199
00:18:19.795 --> 00:18:22.048
No, but you young hyenas did, didn't you?

200
00:18:22.131 --> 00:18:23.299
Huh?

201
00:18:25.134 --> 00:18:28.596
Now, where's that nigger Marcus?
Jake said he did the dirty work.


202
00:18:28.679 --> 00:18:30.348
Is that so?

203
00:18:30.431 --> 00:18:32.433
What do you mean, "nigger"?

204
00:18:33.351 --> 00:18:36.437
I'm asking you if he's the one
who did the beatin', boy.


205
00:18:38.439 --> 00:18:41.651
Y'all better tell the truth,
or I'm gonna lock all of you up.


206
00:18:42.568 --> 00:18:44.862
Mr. Kiner was beating him first.

207
00:18:44.945 --> 00:18:47.573
Kiner shoulda kilt him.
That's what he shoulda done.


208
00:18:51.744 --> 00:18:53.663
Now, y'all stay here.

209
00:18:53.746 --> 00:18:56.666
I'm gonna get some help
and drag that criminal out there.


210
00:18:57.958 --> 00:19:00.294
And don't you all try escaping
like he did.


211
00:19:06.342 --> 00:19:09.428
[Kirky] Hold it! Right in there.
Don't go any further, Bob.


212
00:19:10.680 --> 00:19:12.848
That's it. About in there.
This way a little bit.


213
00:19:13.557 --> 00:19:15.726
-You see anything?
-No.


214
00:19:21.399 --> 00:19:23.526
What's the matter now? 
You giving up?

215
00:19:23.609 --> 00:19:27.196
-You don't think we can get him dragging?
-I know we can't. Haven't had any luck.


216
00:19:34.578 --> 00:19:36.831
Hey. Y'all come down here a minute.

217
00:19:37.581 --> 00:19:39.667
Bet he wants us to dive for Tuck.

218
00:19:40.876 --> 00:19:43.462
Come here. I wanna
talk to you a second.

219
00:19:47.800 --> 00:19:50.720
| just figured a way
| can go easy on you fellas,


220
00:19:50.803 --> 00:19:54.223
and you make yourself, uh,
two bits apiece besides.


221
00:19:54.306 --> 00:19:56.058
How's that?

222
00:19:56.142 --> 00:19:58.227
All you gotta do
is dive down in them shallows


223
00:19:58.310 --> 00:20:00.813
and undo Tuck's body
so's we can haul him in.


224
00:20:00.896 --> 00:20:03.315
-Not for no two bits, we ain't.
-[chuckles]


225
00:20:03.399 --> 00:20:05.693
Listen, I got a lot
on you kids. I can...

226
00:20:07.611 --> 00:20:09.196
Okay, half a buck.

227
00:20:12.324 --> 00:20:13.993
No less than six bits apiece.

228
00:20:14.076 --> 00:20:16.746
Look, I'm doing you a favor.
| could lock you up.


229
00:20:21.208 --> 00:20:23.586
Okay, okay. Six bits. Six bits.

230
00:20:23.669 --> 00:20:24.920
After.

231
00:20:26.255 --> 00:20:28.674
Go back out. They're gonna dive for him.

232
00:20:31.051 --> 00:20:32.803
Go back out over the spot.

233
00:20:35.639 --> 00:20:38.726
The water's pretty dirty. I don't know
if they'll be able to find him.


234
00:20:47.526 --> 00:20:48.611
| found him.

235
00:20:50.070 --> 00:20:52.364
[cheering, laughing]

236
00:20:52.448 --> 00:20:56.076
Here's the rope.
Take that down and tie it on to him.


237
00:21:05.586 --> 00:21:07.087
There it is. They got him.

238
00:21:22.937 --> 00:21:24.939
[men applauding, cheering]

239
00:21:25.022 --> 00:21:26.982
Them little niggers is good swimmers.

240
00:21:27.983 --> 00:21:29.735
What about our money?

241
00:21:29.819 --> 00:21:31.362
Yeah, yeah.

242
00:21:35.366 --> 00:21:36.951
Six bits apiece.

243
00:21:37.535 --> 00:21:39.328
We're short a quarter.

244
00:21:49.046 --> 00:21:51.674
A colored lady and her son
brought these flowers.


245
00:21:51.757 --> 00:21:53.133
You wanna see 'em?

246
00:21:54.343 --> 00:21:57.096
Uh, that'll be all right.
