and we're gonna drink it right here.

492
00:42:13.686 --> 00:42:15.104
It's okay.

493
00:42:16.189 --> 00:42:17.899
We have to go anyway.

494
00:42:17.982 --> 00:42:19.400
You slob.

495
00:42:23.154 --> 00:42:24.238
Here.

496
00:42:25.448 --> 00:42:27.033
Taking these with you?

497
00:42:31.954 --> 00:42:34.957
[chattering resumes]

498
00:42:38.669 --> 00:42:40.171
[klaxon horn honks]

499
00:42:51.766 --> 00:42:53.893
[people chattering]

500
00:42:57.563 --> 00:42:59.273
Wait for me outside.

501
00:43:00.483 --> 00:43:02.735
| gotta see about
this mark she gave me.

502
00:43:02.819 --> 00:43:04.570
Okay. Don't be too long.

503
00:43:10.868 --> 00:43:12.703
Yes, young man? What is it?

504
00:43:14.288 --> 00:43:17.291
| think I should have better than a C
on this paper.


505
00:43:18.292 --> 00:43:21.129
Are you telling me how to grade?

506
00:43:21.212 --> 00:43:24.215
No, I'm just saying
that I think I should have a better mark.


507
00:43:25.508 --> 00:43:29.178
Well, what you think and what I know
are miles apart.


508
00:43:29.262 --> 00:43:32.014
Now, you got a C,
and a C it will stay.

509
00:43:32.807 --> 00:43:34.934
And that brings me to another point.

510
00:43:35.017 --> 00:43:38.146
| was going through your records
yesterday, and I was amazed to notice


511
00:43:38.229 --> 00:43:41.816
that you've signed up
for a college preparatory course.


512
00:43:41.899 --> 00:43:44.777
That's right. I plan on going to college.

513
00:43:44.861 --> 00:43:47.321
-Are you serious?
-Yes.


514
00:43:49.407 --> 00:43:51.492
Well, let me tell you something.

515
00:43:51.576 --> 00:43:53.995
Very few Negro students go to college.

516
00:43:54.787 --> 00:43:56.747
They just aren't college material.

517
00:43:56.831 --> 00:44:01.627
And the few who do go
wind up as cooks and porters in any case.


518
00:44:01.711 --> 00:44:04.755
Now, I just think
that's an awful waste of money and time.


519
00:44:04.839 --> 00:44:08.134
That's not gonna happen to me
whether I go to college or not.


520
00:44:08.217 --> 00:44:10.595
Now, Newton, don't get upset.

521
00:44:10.678 --> 00:44:12.847
I'm here to advise you.

522
00:44:12.930 --> 00:44:15.975
And I advise you
to take a general course.

523
00:44:16.058 --> 00:44:19.854
It'll be much easier for you
and wiser for you.


524
00:44:21.856 --> 00:44:24.859
You just hate us colored kids, don't you?

525
00:44:26.652 --> 00:44:27.737
Young man —

526
00:44:27.820 --> 00:44:29.906
Well, we hate you too.

527
00:44:30.740 --> 00:44:32.533
Every last one of us.

528
00:44:32.617 --> 00:44:37.163
Young man, you and I are going
to the principal's office right now.


529
00:44:37.246 --> 00:44:38.497
Come on.

530
00:44:45.171 --> 00:44:47.423
Newton, you sit right there and wait.

531
00:44:54.764 --> 00:44:56.849
Looks like you're in hot water.

532
00:44:56.933 --> 00:44:58.392
Looks that way.

533
00:45:39.850 --> 00:45:41.560
Newton, come in here.

534
00:45:49.944 --> 00:45:51.320
Sit right there.

535
00:45:53.698 --> 00:45:56.075
Miss McClintock tells me you sassed her.

536
00:45:57.410 --> 00:46:00.830
-Well —
-You accused me of downgrading you.


537
00:46:00.913 --> 00:46:02.456
That right, Newton?

538
00:46:04.166 --> 00:46:06.252
Well, that's not all there was to it.

539
00:46:07.545 --> 00:46:10.089
Well, out with it.
What are you trying to say?


540
00:46:11.340 --> 00:46:13.467
Miss McClintock and |
don't see things the same way.


541
00:46:13.551 --> 00:46:15.469
Miss McClintock
happens to be your instructor


542
00:46:15.553 --> 00:46:17.972
as well as your guidance teacher.

543
00:46:18.055 --> 00:46:20.433
| just don't like the way
she wants to guide me.


544
00:46:20.516 --> 00:46:23.352
And that caused you to, uh,
tell her you hated her?


545
00:46:23.436 --> 00:46:26.314
-Well, I didn't say —
-Don't lie. You know you said it.


546
00:46:27.690 --> 00:46:29.525
| didn't say I hated you alone.

547
00:46:29.608 --> 00:46:31.777
| said all the colored kids hate you.

548
00:46:31.861 --> 00:46:33.654
And we do.

549
00:46:33.738 --> 00:46:37.742
-Why do you say such a thing?
-She's always telling us the same thing.


550
00:46:37.825 --> 00:46:41.078
"Don't go to college.
You're just gonna be porters and maids."


551
00:46:41.162 --> 00:46:42.830
Is this true, Miss McClintock?

552
00:46:42.913 --> 00:46:45.082
Do you tell the Negro students
such things?


553
00:46:45.166 --> 00:46:48.836
Mr. Hall, I have been class adviser here
for over 20 years.


554
00:46:48.919 --> 00:46:51.422
| tell them
what I was instructed to tell them.


555
00:46:51.505 --> 00:46:53.132
Who? Who instructed you?

556
00:46:53.215 --> 00:46:55.926
Mr. Hornsby, the principal before you.

557
00:46:57.094 --> 00:46:59.638
Oh, I see, I see. Hmm.

558
00:46:59.722 --> 00:47:01.140
Miss McClintock —

559
00:47:02.016 --> 00:47:03.351
Well, that'll be all.

560
00:47:04.226 --> 00:47:06.062
| would like to talk to Newton.

561
00:47:13.069 --> 00:47:14.862
Why don't you sit over here?

562
00:47:20.743 --> 00:47:22.870
To explain Miss McClintock, uh...

563
00:47:24.872 --> 00:47:29.418
one would have to go back to a tragic time
before either you or I was born.


564
00:47:30.836 --> 00:47:34.507
And although she must share the blame
for this awful wrong,


565
00:47:34.590 --> 00:47:36.926
Miss McClintock
is somewhat a victim herself.


566
00:47:37.009 --> 00:47:42.181
She thought it was right because it was
a situation that existed for so long.


567
00:47:45.351 --> 00:47:47.353
Mr. Hornsby is more to blame than she.

568
00:47:51.440 --> 00:47:54.610
But then, so is his father.

569
00:47:55.694 --> 00:47:56.987
And my father.

570
00:47:58.531 --> 00:48:00.074
And millions of others.

571
00:48:02.868 --> 00:48:04.036
Now,

572
00:48:04.912 --> 00:48:08.207
there are still things at this school
that I don't like, Newton —


573
00:48:09.166 --> 00:48:12.711
the fact that you boys can't play
on the football and basketball teams,


574
00:48:12.795 --> 00:48:15.423
that you can't attend
the school dances and parties.


575
00:48:16.132 --> 00:48:19.468
If it were left up to me
and a few others who care,


576
00:48:19.552 --> 00:48:21.011
all this would stop.

577
00:48:21.095 --> 00:48:24.265
But there are still
too many Mr. Hornsbys left around.


578
00:48:26.767 --> 00:48:27.852
But...

579
00:48:28.686 --> 00:48:31.814
well, maybe someday. [chuckles]

580
00:48:34.692 --> 00:48:38.112
[sighs] You can go now, Newton.

581
00:48:38.195 --> 00:48:41.866
| intend to have a long talk
with Miss McClintock


582
00:48:41.949 --> 00:48:44.952
and a few of the other teachers
when the board meets next.


583
00:48:46.454 --> 00:48:49.707
I'm sure that their attitudes
and thinking...


584
00:48:51.709 --> 00:48:53.294
they'll be different.

585
00:48:56.088 --> 00:48:57.423
Oh, Newton,

586
00:48:58.674 --> 00:49:01.760
you're to show Miss McClintock
the highest respect.


587
00:49:01.844 --> 00:49:02.845
Hmm?

588
00:49:25.075 --> 00:49:27.328
Hello, Newt. Jappy.

589
00:49:28.120 --> 00:49:30.164
Where is Arcella?

590
00:49:30.247 --> 00:49:32.708
Oh. I thought she'd be home by now.

591
00:49:32.791 --> 00:49:35.294
| had to stay —
We had to stay late.

592
00:49:37.004 --> 00:49:40.466
Oh, she said something about
going to the library before it closed.


593
00:49:40.549 --> 00:49:44.178
Oh, I see.
Well, I'll tell her you boys stopped by.


594
00:49:46.555 --> 00:49:47.681
Oh, Newt?

595
00:49:49.225 --> 00:49:51.268
Come here a minute.

596
00:49:51.352 --> 00:49:53.270
| thought I ought to tell you.

597
00:49:53.354 --> 00:49:56.565
Arcella's birthday
is the 27th of next month.


598
00:49:56.649 --> 00:49:59.193
-Oh, thank you. Thank you very much.
-Okay.


599
00:50:02.530 --> 00:50:04.031
[door shuts]

600
00:50:05.157 --> 00:50:07.409
Arcella's sure enough at the library.

601
00:50:07.493 --> 00:50:09.495
What's it to you where she's at?

602
00:50:09.578 --> 00:50:11.705
It's okay, it's okay. I just asked.

603
00:50:22.258 --> 00:50:23.551
| gotta go.

604
00:50:26.303 --> 00:50:27.805
Hello, Newt.

605
00:50:27.888 --> 00:50:29.390
Hello, Arcella.

606
00:50:30.057 --> 00:50:32.268
You wanna go for a little walk?

607
00:50:32.351 --> 00:50:33.394
No.

608
00:50:36.939 --> 00:50:38.649
I'm sorry.

609
00:50:38.732 --> 00:50:42.486
| have to get in the house and do
some homework and a few things.


610
00:50:42.570 --> 00:50:43.862
| could help.

611
00:50:46.073 --> 00:50:47.074
No.

612
00:50:48.409 --> 00:50:49.827
No.

613
00:50:49.910 --> 00:50:51.954
You wanna go to the show tomorrow?

614
00:50:53.205 --> 00:50:55.082
I'm sorry, Newt. I can't.

615
00:50:57.501 --> 00:50:59.086
Is something wrong?

616
00:51:00.129 --> 00:51:01.171
Wrong?

617
00:51:02.214 --> 00:51:05.134
No. Why did you say that, anyway?

618
00:51:07.094 --> 00:51:09.513
It's nothin'. I just asked.

619
00:51:13.517 --> 00:51:15.102
I'll be going now.

620
00:51:21.400 --> 00:51:23.902
| told your mother
you went to the library.


621
00:51:38.959 --> 00:51:40.169
[engine stops]

622
00:51:42.630 --> 00:51:44.089
Hiya, Son.

623
00:51:47.301 --> 00:51:50.137
Nobody told me you was gettin' out today.

624
00:51:53.390 --> 00:51:55.142
You his old man?

625
00:51:55.225 --> 00:51:56.518
That's right.

626
00:51:56.602 --> 00:51:58.354
You have to sign this here paper.

627
00:52:00.397 --> 00:52:02.941
-What's all this for?
-He's on probation.


628
00:52:03.025 --> 00:52:06.028
That means we turn him over to you.
Sign it right here.


629
00:52:07.655 --> 00:52:08.656
[spits]

630
00:52:16.372 --> 00:52:19.541
Hell, boy, that ain't no signature.
That's an X.


631
00:52:21.877 --> 00:52:26.131
How old's a man gotta be
'fore you people stop callin' him "boy"?


632
00:52:27.007 --> 00:52:31.095
Now, if it's my signature you want,
as you call it,


633
00:52:31.178 --> 00:52:32.471
that's it.

634
00:52:32.554 --> 00:52:34.515
Take it or leave it.

635
00:52:35.307 --> 00:52:37.017
He can't write.

636
00:52:38.185 --> 00:52:40.896
You better keep your ass
out of trouble, boy.


637
00:52:40.979 --> 00:52:42.981
Next time we're gonna throw away
the key on you.


638
00:52:43.065 --> 00:52:45.526
[dog barks, whines]

639
00:52:51.865 --> 00:52:54.118
[engine starts]

640
00:52:56.245 --> 00:52:59.873
"Boy." "Boy."
That's all those people know.


641
00:53:00.582 --> 00:53:04.211
They'd call Jesus Christ "boy"
if he was black.


642
00:53:06.255 --> 00:53:09.091
Got so I hate the
sight of a white man.

643
00:53:15.222 --> 00:53:16.849
'Tain't much.

644
00:53:16.932 --> 00:53:19.727
I'd have done better
if I had heard you was comin'.


645
00:53:28.527 --> 00:53:30.863
Well, come on, boy. 
Get something to eat.

646
00:53:47.880 --> 00:53:49.840
How'd they treat you up there?

647
00:53:58.766 --> 00:54:03.145
I-I meant to come to see you,
but things got busy around here.


648
00:54:07.524 --> 00:54:09.526
Well, you're glad to be back, ain't ya?

649
00:54:13.864 --> 00:54:15.449
Did they beat up on ya?

650
00:54:21.330 --> 00:54:23.332
Those sons of bitches.

651
00:54:24.750 --> 00:54:27.628
I'll kill me a peckerwood sure as hell
one of these days.


652
00:54:28.337 --> 00:54:30.172
The dirty, lousy...

653
00:54:37.721 --> 00:54:39.473
Hey — Hey —

654
00:54:40.307 --> 00:54:43.143
What's the matter, Son?
You hurtin' or somethin'?


655
00:54:59.910 --> 00:55:02.204
[Newt] What's Doc Cravens's car
doing here?


656
00:55:02.287 --> 00:55:04.581
Mama came home from work
with a dizzy spell.


657
00:55:06.208 --> 00:55:08.252
Is she real sick?

658
00:55:08.335 --> 00:55:10.170
Don't think so.

659
00:55:10.254 --> 00:55:12.089
Doc ought to be out soon.

660
00:55:16.176 --> 00:55:18.303
You worried about Marcus coming home?

661
00:55:19.012 --> 00:55:20.222
No.

662
00:55:20.305 --> 00:55:21.431
You sure?

663
00:55:22.641 --> 00:55:24.017
Yeah, I'm sure.

664
00:55:25.811 --> 00:55:27.563
How about a few boxing lessons?

665
00:55:27.646 --> 00:55:28.856
What for?

666
00:55:28.939 --> 00:55:31.483
Oh, just for the fun of it.
Come on. Come on.


667
00:55:33.110 --> 00:55:35.571
Now, the right up. Elbow down.

668
00:55:35.654 --> 00:55:38.615
Now, left, left. Throw it.
Throw the right. Throw it.


669
00:55:38.699 --> 00:55:39.867
[groans]

670
00:55:40.909 --> 00:55:42.452
Now, let that teach ya.

671
00:55:43.495 --> 00:55:46.248
Never leave your belly wide open
like that again.


672
00:55:52.629 --> 00:55:55.716
See that she gets two of these
every four hours, Jack.


673
00:55:56.842 --> 00:55:59.636
-Call me if you need me.
-Thanks, Tim.


674
00:55:59.720 --> 00:56:01.179
Hiya, Newt.

675
00:56:01.263 --> 00:56:03.640
-You look all tuckered out.
-How's Mama?


676
00:56:04.600 --> 00:56:07.728
She's all right.
Just needs a couple of days' quiet.


677
00:56:10.063 --> 00:56:13.108
Come on in the house, boy.
| want to talk to you some.


678
00:56:13.191 --> 00:56:14.443
[car door shuts]

679
00:56:14.526 --> 00:56:16.612
[engine starts]

680
00:56:16.695 --> 00:56:19.072
[car drives away]

681
00:56:25.621 --> 00:56:28.624
What happened between you
and that Jefferson girl?


682
00:56:30.334 --> 00:56:31.460
Nothin'.

683
00:56:32.753 --> 00:56:34.671
She's actin' kinda funny.

684
00:56:34.755 --> 00:56:37.257
| want the truth, boy. You hear me?

685
00:56:37.341 --> 00:56:40.135
-It's nothing serious, Papa.
-Nothing serious?


686
00:56:40.218 --> 00:56:43.639
Her pa was here this afternoon
saying she's gonna have a baby.


687
00:56:43.722 --> 00:56:46.308
-Ain't that serious?
-[Sarah] Jack, is that Newt?


688
00:56:46.391 --> 00:56:48.477
| want the truth, boy. You hear me?

689
00:56:48.560 --> 00:56:50.604
[Sarah] What's going on down there?

690
00:56:50.687 --> 00:56:52.856
Sarah,
you shouldn't be bothered with this.


691
00:56:52.940 --> 00:56:55.150
| want to know what's going on.

692
00:56:55.233 --> 00:56:57.861
Well, I might as well tell you.

693
00:56:58.570 --> 00:57:01.156
Jefferson was over to see me
about his daughter Arcella.


694
00:57:01.239 --> 00:57:04.660
-What's wrong with her?
-Well, says she's gonna have a baby.


695
00:57:04.743 --> 00:57:06.954
Thinks Newt here
had something to do with it.


696
00:57:08.747 --> 00:57:10.207
Oh, my Lord.

697
00:57:13.585 --> 00:57:14.920
Son?

698
00:57:15.003 --> 00:57:19.174
Mama... I didn't do nothin' like that.

699
00:57:19.967 --> 00:57:21.343
You sure, Son?

700
00:57:22.135 --> 00:57:23.428
I'm sure, Ma.

701
00:57:25.097 --> 00:57:26.848
| love Arcella.

702
00:57:30.310 --> 00:57:32.354
[Sarah] He's telling the truth.

703
00:57:35.649 --> 00:57:37.651
I'm sure he's telling the truth.

704
00:57:40.862 --> 00:57:44.574
We just have to
face the girl with him

705
00:57:44.658 --> 00:57:47.369
and then see what she says.

706
00:57:48.495 --> 00:57:52.040
-Sarah, you have to stay in bed.
-I'm going, Jack. I'm going with him.


707
00:57:52.124 --> 00:57:53.583
-[groans]
-Sarah!


708
00:57:53.667 --> 00:57:54.751
Mom.

709
00:57:54.835 --> 00:57:58.046
Sarah, don't worry about nothin'.

710
00:57:58.130 --> 00:58:00.215
I'll go with him to see the Jeffersons.

711
00:58:00.298 --> 00:58:02.634
Speak up, girl.

712
00:58:02.718 --> 00:58:04.720
Is this boy responsible or not?

713
00:58:04.803 --> 00:58:07.055
No, Papa! Why don't you listen?

714
00:58:07.139 --> 00:58:10.100
Then who was it? Who was it?

715
00:58:10.183 --> 00:58:14.271
Bob. Bob. Do you want to tell
the whole neighborhood?


716
00:58:14.354 --> 00:58:18.191
Arcella. Baby, tell Mother.

717
00:58:18.275 --> 00:58:20.318
-Newt!
-I'll help you, honey.


718
00:58:20.402 --> 00:58:23.196
Newt. Newt. [sobbing]

719
00:58:27.951 --> 00:58:29.411
I'm sorry.

720
00:58:31.079 --> 00:58:33.915
I'm sorry Papa got you mixed up
in all this.


721
00:58:36.251 --> 00:58:38.795
And I'm sorry for what has happened.

722
00:58:44.051 --> 00:58:45.969
| guess that's all I can say.

723
00:58:50.015 --> 00:58:52.267
You will try to forgive me, won't you?

724
00:59:04.154 --> 00:59:08.116
Papa, you wanted to know who it was?

725
00:59:08.200 --> 00:59:09.284
Well?

726
00:59:13.246 --> 00:59:17.042
It was Chauncey. 
Chauncey Cavanaugh.

727
00:59:17.125 --> 00:59:18.835
[Arcella sobs]

728
00:59:18.919 --> 00:59:20.629
[mother] Oh, my Lord.

729
00:59:21.463 --> 00:59:23.340
Oh, my Lord.

730
00:59:29.471 --> 00:59:33.391
[Newt] Uncle Rob, why do white people
do so many awful things?


731
00:59:33.475 --> 00:59:35.685
Is a white boy responsible for Arcella?

732
00:59:35.769 --> 00:59:37.312
Yes, Sir.

733
00:59:38.480 --> 00:59:40.190
Chauncey Cavanaugh.

734
00:59:41.149 --> 00:59:44.736
Newt, I've been blind for 30 years.

735
00:59:46.571 --> 00:59:49.407
| don't know
what color people are anymore.


736
00:59:50.909 --> 00:59:54.746
If somebody does something, good or bad,

737
00:59:55.622 --> 00:59:57.666
| don't figure his color into it.

738
00:59:59.292 --> 01:00:00.794
| figure his deed.

739
01:00:06.258 --> 01:00:09.636
Do you remember what it was like
before the explosion?


740
01:00:10.720 --> 01:00:14.683
What color the sky was? 
Things like that?

741
01:00:15.517 --> 01:00:17.269
[chuckles]

742
01:00:18.812 --> 01:00:22.149
