01:19:07.898 --> 01:19:11.318
Should've asked yourself that before
you clobbered him with that crowbar.


977
01:19:11.402 --> 01:19:14.280
Crowbar? What crowbar?
| ain't seen no crowbar!


978
01:19:14.363 --> 01:19:17.366
-Why don't you tell me the truth?
-All right, that's enough, Kirky!


979
01:19:18.492 --> 01:19:21.328
Any more questions,
you can come back tomorrow morning.


980
01:19:25.374 --> 01:19:26.375
[door shuts]

981
01:19:26.458 --> 01:19:28.836
| didn't kill nobody, Doc.
| didn't kill nobody!


982
01:19:42.391 --> 01:19:44.393
Did Mary Kiner take it hard?

983
01:19:44.476 --> 01:19:47.688
Yep. Saddest funeral service
I've ever seen.


984
01:19:47.771 --> 01:19:50.607
Poor woman's loaded down with grief.

985
01:19:50.691 --> 01:19:52.943
Sure glad a black man didn't do it.

986
01:19:59.575 --> 01:20:00.993
[Pete] Hurry up, Newt.

987
01:20:16.508 --> 01:20:17.676
Pete?

988
01:20:19.428 --> 01:20:20.846
Yeah?

989
01:20:20.929 --> 01:20:24.975
What did Papa mean by, "There'd be trouble
if a Negro had killed Mr. Kiner"?


990
01:20:25.059 --> 01:20:26.310
Meant just what he said.

991
01:20:26.393 --> 01:20:30.356
It could be real trouble, like they had
over in Bartsville a couple of years back.


992
01:20:30.439 --> 01:20:32.983
Freddie Sears shot a white man
who hit his sister.


993
01:20:34.151 --> 01:20:35.986
What happened?

994
01:20:36.070 --> 01:20:39.948
Well, the whites lynched Freddie
and burned down half the Negro homes.


995
01:20:41.658 --> 01:20:43.869
I'm glad you don't know nothing about it.

996
01:20:43.952 --> 01:20:46.705
That way you don't have to
open your mouth. Understand?


997
01:20:46.789 --> 01:20:48.123
Yeah.

998
01:20:51.335 --> 01:20:54.338
[people chattering]

999
01:21:00.594 --> 01:21:03.555
Stay out of it, now.
Just stop right there!


1000
01:21:03.639 --> 01:21:05.641
-Bye-bye, Silas.
-Hangin' is too good for ya!


1001
01:21:05.724 --> 01:21:07.643
You don't look so happy now,
you old buzzard!


1002
01:21:07.726 --> 01:21:09.895
They gonna string you up, Silas.

1003
01:21:09.978 --> 01:21:11.355
[man] You gonna hang!

1004
01:21:12.606 --> 01:21:16.151
The witnesses and brutal evidence

1005
01:21:16.235 --> 01:21:19.863
will bring home to you
more than any statement of mine


1006
01:21:19.947 --> 01:21:22.324
the vileness of this offense

1007
01:21:22.408 --> 01:21:25.494
against heaven and all humanity.

1008
01:21:27.663 --> 01:21:31.458
And there,
gentlemen and ladies of the jury,


1009
01:21:32.042 --> 01:21:33.919
there sits the beast who is responsible —

1010
01:21:34.002 --> 01:21:36.797
Your Honor, I object to such reference
to the defendant.


1011
01:21:36.880 --> 01:21:38.966
[judge] Objection sustained.

1012
01:21:39.049 --> 01:21:41.093
Watch your language, Counselor.

1013
01:21:41.176 --> 01:21:42.761
I'm sorry, Your Honor.

1014
01:21:46.807 --> 01:21:50.853
We intend to prove that the defendant did,

1015
01:21:50.936 --> 01:21:53.564
with premeditation and willfulness,

1016
01:21:54.314 --> 01:21:57.609
murder the deceased with this crowbar.

1017
01:21:59.111 --> 01:22:02.406
Circumstantial evidence
isn't always enough.


1018
01:22:04.658 --> 01:22:07.870
We beg you to judge
this defendant's guilt or innocence


1019
01:22:07.953 --> 01:22:11.999
solely upon the events, uh,
presented in this case.


1020
01:22:14.835 --> 01:22:19.548
With that, I place the fate
of the defendant in your hands.


1021
01:22:20.674 --> 01:22:21.800
Thank you.

1022
01:22:23.635 --> 01:22:27.306
[Judge Cavanaugh] Because of the
late start, court will adjourn until 1:00.


1023
01:22:27.389 --> 01:22:31.310
We can expect to hear from the state's
witnesses at that time, Counsel?


1024
01:22:31.393 --> 01:22:33.103
We shall be ready, Your Honor.

1025
01:22:33.187 --> 01:22:35.189
-Court is dismissed.
-[gavel raps]


1026
01:22:41.695 --> 01:22:44.114
[wolf whistle]

1027
01:22:50.621 --> 01:22:52.414
[man] He looked guilty as hell to me.

1028
01:22:52.498 --> 01:22:55.334
Old McCormack'll make a dunce
out of that kid lawyer.


1029
01:22:55.417 --> 01:22:56.960
[man 2 chuckles]
Old Silas really jumped


1030
01:22:57.044 --> 01:22:59.254
when McCormack slammed that crowbar
on the table.


1031
01:22:59.338 --> 01:23:01.465
[man] Silas ain't got a sucker's chance.

1032
01:23:01.548 --> 01:23:03.091
What else did you see,

1033
01:23:03.175 --> 01:23:06.345
other than the deceased and the defendant
lying on the floor?


1034
01:23:07.346 --> 01:23:11.934
A hoe and a whip
and that crowbar la yin' over there.


1035
01:23:12.017 --> 01:23:14.102
It was between Jake and Silas.

1036
01:23:15.020 --> 01:23:17.231
What else do you recall?

1037
01:23:17.814 --> 01:23:22.402
He was ea yin', "I'm gonna get my money
from that old skinflint or die tr yin'


1038
01:23:23.946 --> 01:23:25.948
and something about, "Over my dead body."

1039
01:23:26.031 --> 01:23:28.492
To whom was he saying this?

1040
01:23:28.575 --> 01:23:30.702
To Booker Savage in Chappie Logan's place.

1041
01:23:31.370 --> 01:23:33.539
[McCormack] Thank you, young lady.
That will be all.


1042
01:23:33.622 --> 01:23:38.085
He said he was goin' back for
his day's pay. He told me that, all right.


1043
01:23:38.168 --> 01:23:40.462
Did he seem angry?

1044
01:23:40.546 --> 01:23:42.756
Oh, he was fussin' some.

1045
01:23:44.383 --> 01:23:45.926
Thank you. That will be all.

1046
01:24:03.986 --> 01:24:05.404
[door shuts]

1047
01:24:13.829 --> 01:24:15.122
Newt?

1048
01:24:16.915 --> 01:24:21.044
-Mama, I got something to tell you.
-What's troubling you, Son?


1049
01:24:24.172 --> 01:24:26.508
Silas didn't kill Mr. Kiner.

1050
01:24:27.676 --> 01:24:29.094
| saw the whole thing.

1051
01:24:30.178 --> 01:24:32.014
It all happened so fast.

1052
01:24:33.056 --> 01:24:35.559
[Sarah] Go on, Son. Finish it.

1053
01:24:37.269 --> 01:24:39.104
| was up in the hayloft.

1054
01:24:42.691 --> 01:24:45.444
-Go on.
-And then Mrs. Kiner came in.


1055
01:24:45.527 --> 01:24:47.904
She was screaming and everything.

1056
01:24:48.864 --> 01:24:51.116
And then she went out,

1057
01:24:51.199 --> 01:24:53.160
| got down and went home.

1058
01:24:54.453 --> 01:24:55.662
| guess that's all.

1059
01:24:59.499 --> 01:25:01.627
This is incredible.

1060
01:25:02.586 --> 01:25:04.880
Newt, have you told
anyone else about this?


1061
01:25:04.963 --> 01:25:06.423
Just Mama and Papa.

1062
01:25:09.343 --> 01:25:11.136
Well, Sarah, Jack,

1063
01:25:11.219 --> 01:25:13.930
it would be wrong for me
as the judge in this case


1064
01:25:14.014 --> 01:25:15.641
to divulge this information.

1065
01:25:15.724 --> 01:25:17.100
You'll have to do it.

1066
01:25:17.184 --> 01:25:20.771
The man who should get this information
is Harley Davis, Silas's attorney.


1067
01:25:21.438 --> 01:25:24.274
-Are you willing to do that?
-If that's what you want.


1068
01:25:25.692 --> 01:25:28.487
Now, Newton here will have to
take the stand and testify.


1069
01:25:28.570 --> 01:25:31.907
It's going to be rough on the boy,
but there's simply no other way.


1070
01:25:36.745 --> 01:25:40.874
| think you'd better go and have a talk
with Mr. Davis just as soon as possible.


1071
01:25:40.957 --> 01:25:43.585
He's staying
at Jenny Brighton's boardinghouse.


1072
01:25:49.466 --> 01:25:50.967
Thank you, Judge.

1073
01:25:54.888 --> 01:25:55.889
Jack.

1074
01:25:57.432 --> 01:26:00.519
Could I speak to you and Sarah
for just a minute?


1075
01:26:00.602 --> 01:26:02.145
Go ahead, Son.

1076
01:26:05.440 --> 01:26:09.152
-About Chauncey and the Jefferson girl.
-[door shuts]


1077
01:26:09.236 --> 01:26:13.532
I'll personally see to it
that Chauncey takes care of the baby.


1078
01:26:13.615 --> 01:26:14.616
I..o

1079
01:26:15.826 --> 01:26:17.369
[sighs] I'm sorry.

1080
01:26:22.999 --> 01:26:24.960
Mr. Davis, you may call your witness.

1081
01:26:25.043 --> 01:26:26.628
Thank you, Your Honor.

1082
01:26:28.046 --> 01:26:30.006
Would Newton Winger please take the stand?

1083
01:26:31.049 --> 01:26:33.301
[spectators murmuring]

1084
01:26:42.519 --> 01:26:44.438
[murmuring subsides]

1085
01:27:01.663 --> 01:27:04.207
Please stand and raise your right hand.

1086
01:27:05.751 --> 01:27:08.003
Do you solemnly swear to tell the truth,
the whole truth,


1087
01:27:08.086 --> 01:27:10.005
and nothing but the truth,
so help you God?


1088
01:27:10.088 --> 01:27:11.882
-Yes, sir.
-Be seated, please.


1089
01:27:17.053 --> 01:27:19.306
Would you tell the court your full name?

1090
01:27:19.389 --> 01:27:22.142
Newt — Newton Buchanan Winger.

1091
01:27:22.225 --> 01:27:24.978
-How old are you, Newton?
-Fifteen.


1092
01:27:26.688 --> 01:27:29.399
Would you speak
just a little louder, Newt?


1093
01:27:30.734 --> 01:27:33.111
Did you know the deceased, Jake Kiner?

1094
01:27:33.987 --> 01:27:34.988
Yes, Sir.

1095
01:27:35.071 --> 01:27:37.407
And what was the last day
you worked for him?


1096
01:27:37.491 --> 01:27:38.658
June the 14th.

1097
01:27:38.742 --> 01:27:42.162
-On the day that Mr. Kiner was killed?
-Yes, sir.


1098
01:27:42.245 --> 01:27:47.000
Now, Newt, I want you to tell the court
in your own words exactly what happened.


1099
01:27:47.083 --> 01:27:50.212
Well, I was eating my lunch
up in the hayloft,


1100
01:27:50.295 --> 01:27:52.047
and I heard some noise down below.

1101
01:27:52.130 --> 01:27:54.007
What kind of noise?

1102
01:27:54.090 --> 01:27:55.967
Somebody was rippin' off the door

1103
01:27:56.051 --> 01:27:59.971
to where Mr. Kiner keeps his peach brandy
and cider and stuff with a crowbar.


1104
01:28:00.055 --> 01:28:01.681
And what happened then?

1105
01:28:01.765 --> 01:28:05.352
Mr. Kiner and Mr. Newhall came in,
fussin' about something.


1106
01:28:05.435 --> 01:28:07.813
Mr. Kiner got real mad.

1107
01:28:07.896 --> 01:28:10.899
He started hitting Mr. Newhall
with his whip handle.


1108
01:28:10.982 --> 01:28:13.401
Mr. Newhall tried to grab the hoe,

1109
01:28:13.485 --> 01:28:16.404
but Mr. Kiner knocked him down
before he could get a blow in.


1110
01:28:16.488 --> 01:28:19.741
-[spectators murmuring]
-And then he saw this other man.


1111
01:28:19.825 --> 01:28:22.911
But the other man hit him in the head
with the crowbar,


1112
01:28:22.994 --> 01:28:25.413
and he kept beating after he was down.

1113
01:28:25.497 --> 01:28:27.415
[spectators gasping, murmuring]

1114
01:28:27.499 --> 01:28:30.377
Newt, I want you to tell the court

1115
01:28:30.460 --> 01:28:33.713
why you didn't come forth
with this information before.


1116
01:28:36.258 --> 01:28:39.511
-Well, I was scared.
-Scared of what?


1117
01:28:39.594 --> 01:28:42.013
| thought it might cause some trouble

1118
01:28:43.265 --> 01:28:45.559
"tween the white folks
and the colored folks here.


1119
01:28:45.642 --> 01:28:49.312
Now, Newt, I want you to
look around this room very carefully


1120
01:28:49.396 --> 01:28:51.606
and tell the court
if you see the man,

1121
01:28:51.690 --> 01:28:54.568
the one who broke into the room
and beat Mr. Kiner.


1122
01:28:58.822 --> 01:28:59.865
It's him.

1123
01:28:59.948 --> 01:29:04.244
The — The man with the red shirt on.
Booker Savage.


1124
01:29:04.327 --> 01:29:08.039
-[murmuring continues]
-He's lyin'! He's lyin"!


1125
01:29:10.125 --> 01:29:11.751
[gavel raps]

1126
01:29:11.835 --> 01:29:13.753
Order! Order!

1127
01:29:16.715 --> 01:29:18.675
[murmuring subsides]

1128
01:29:19.676 --> 01:29:21.469
Proceed, Counsel.

1129
01:29:21.553 --> 01:29:23.471
-That's all, Newt.
-Cross-examine.


1130
01:29:23.555 --> 01:29:25.307
Prosecution waives.

1131
01:29:25.390 --> 01:29:26.683
You may step down.

1132
01:29:28.310 --> 01:29:30.896
Your Honor, the defense requests

1133
01:29:30.979 --> 01:29:33.690
that this man, Booker Savage,
take the stand.


1134
01:29:33.773 --> 01:29:37.319
[Judge Cavanaugh] Officer Kirky, would you
please escort Mr. Savage to the stand?


1135
01:29:38.653 --> 01:29:41.239
[spectators murmuring, exclaiming]

1136
01:29:42.574 --> 01:29:46.202
-Get that nigger!
-[spectators clamoring]


1137
01:29:47.162 --> 01:29:49.497
-Order! Order!
-Kill him! Kill him!


1138
01:29:49.581 --> 01:29:52.334
Kill that black bastard! 
String him up!

1139
01:29:52.417 --> 01:29:54.336
-[Kirky] Stay there!
-Order! Order!


1140
01:29:54.419 --> 01:29:56.129
[groans]

1141
01:29:58.632 --> 01:30:00.675
[pistol cocks]

1142
01:30:06.556 --> 01:30:08.725
Now, just hold it! Hold it! He's trapped.

1143
01:30:08.808 --> 01:30:11.770
The door to the outside is locked anyway.
Just stand back.


1144
01:30:13.730 --> 01:30:15.106
[gunshot]

1145
01:30:22.656 --> 01:30:26.451
[spectators murmuring]

1146
01:30:30.664 --> 01:30:33.833
-Back to your seats. Back to your seats.
-[gavel raps]


1147
01:30:38.755 --> 01:30:40.548
He shot himself dead.

1148
01:30:46.972 --> 01:30:48.515
Well, Counsel,

1149
01:30:49.975 --> 01:30:51.393
it looks like your move.

1150
01:30:52.435 --> 01:30:53.478
Your Honor,

1151
01:30:53.561 --> 01:30:58.233
in view of all that has taken place here
before us today,


1152
01:30:59.275 --> 01:31:04.531
the state wishes to withdraw all charges
against the defendant, Silas Newhall,


1153
01:31:04.614 --> 01:31:06.324
if the court will permit.

1154
01:31:06.408 --> 01:31:07.867
The court will permit.

1155
01:31:09.953 --> 01:31:13.999
| now order the defendant released.
This case is closed.


1156
01:31:15.333 --> 01:31:20.422
But I would like to say this.

1157
01:31:20.505 --> 01:31:22.549
We have a judicial system in this country

1158
01:31:22.632 --> 01:31:25.635
that gives every man the right
to a fair trial when accused.


1159
01:31:26.928 --> 01:31:29.347
You who shouted so viciously

1160
01:31:29.431 --> 01:31:31.349
frightened Booker Savage
out of that right.


1161
01:31:31.433 --> 01:31:33.101
You pulled the trigger.

1162
01:31:36.938 --> 01:31:39.399
You decided
that he had killed a white man,


1163
01:31:40.608 --> 01:31:43.737
So you judged him, and you executed him.

1164
01:31:44.446 --> 01:31:46.698
Have you forgotten that
it was a black boy

1165
01:31:46.781 --> 01:31:50.368
who saved a white man's life here
just a few minutes ago?


1166
01:31:50.452 --> 01:31:52.662
It took courage to do that.

1167
01:31:52.746 --> 01:31:55.248
A lot more courage than you have.

1168
01:31:56.291 --> 01:32:00.003
It was what he feared from you
that kept him from revealing what he knew.


1169
01:32:00.920 --> 01:32:03.798
And your actions justified that fear.

1170
01:32:05.592 --> 01:32:08.219
This moment should haunt
your minds forever.


1171
01:32:10.472 --> 01:32:12.432
This court is dismissed.

1172
01:32:25.487 --> 01:32:27.530
Newt? Newt?

1173
01:32:29.532 --> 01:32:32.535
It was a good thing you did, Newt.
A brave thing.


1174
01:32:32.619 --> 01:32:34.537
We're both thankful to you.

1175
01:32:35.663 --> 01:32:37.791
Thank you, Newt.

1176
01:32:37.874 --> 01:32:39.751
Thank you.

1177
01:32:39.834 --> 01:32:43.713
No matter what you're thinking, Son,
you did the right thing.


1178
01:32:44.923 --> 01:32:48.551
We're sorry about Booker and Marcus, but...

1179
01:32:48.635 --> 01:32:49.803
Oh, Jack!

1180
01:32:49.886 --> 01:32:52.263
Newt, get Doc Cravens.

1181
01:32:52.931 --> 01:32:54.140
Hurry!

1182
01:32:54.224 --> 01:32:55.642
What's the matter?

1183
01:33:01.356 --> 01:33:03.274
-Marcus.
-Yeah?


1184
01:33:05.318 --> 01:33:07.153
| have some bad news for you.

1185
01:33:10.615 --> 01:33:11.950
Your pa is dead.

1186
01:33:14.160 --> 01:33:16.955
He just shot hisself
over at the courthouse.


1187
01:33:18.623 --> 01:33:22.210
Why? Why did he do that?

1188
01:33:23.253 --> 01:33:25.004
Turns out he killed old man Kiner.

1189
01:33:26.131 --> 01:33:27.757
It all happened just now

1190
01:33:28.591 --> 01:33:30.135
at the trial.

1191
01:33:49.279 --> 01:33:51.447
What happened to my old man?

1192
01:33:52.532 --> 01:33:55.451
He shot hisself with my gun.
That's what happened to him.


1193
01:33:55.535 --> 01:33:58.538
He didn't kill old man Kiner,
and I know it.


1194
01:33:58.621 --> 01:34:02.417
Well, Newt Winger says different.
And he saw it all, every damn bit of it.


1195
01:34:02.500 --> 01:34:04.627
I'm gonna kill that bastard.

1196
01:34:40.496 --> 01:34:41.706
Jack?

1197
01:34:50.256 --> 01:34:54.302
You'd better come up.
Sarah's asking for Newt.


1198
01:35:10.777 --> 01:35:11.778
Mama?

1199
01:35:34.175 --> 01:35:35.218
Mama?

1200
01:35:43.101 --> 01:35:46.396
Newt, your mother's gone.

1201
01:35:49.399 --> 01:35:50.483
Newt.

1202
01:36:09.877 --> 01:36:11.504
Come on, boy.

1203
01:36:38.156 --> 01:36:42.327
[train whistle blowing in distance]

1204
01:37:19.405 --> 01:37:22.408
[train whistle continues blowing, faint]

1205
01:38:40.278 --> 01:38:42.029
| ain't afraid, Mama.

1206
01:38:46.659 --> 01:38:48.578
| ain't afraid anymore.

1207
01:38:52.165 --> 01:38:53.499
[exhales]

1208
01:40:23.506 --> 01:40:26.759
This is the last resting place
of Sarah Winger,


1209
01:40:27.593 --> 01:40:31.347
to await resurrection
in the Lord Jesus Christ.


1210
01:40:31.430 --> 01:40:35.268
Sarah Winger,
who gave of her love, her hope,


1211
01:40:35.351 --> 01:40:37.353
understanding and devotion

1212
01:40:38.187 --> 01:40:41.566
to her family and
to all who knew her.

1213
01:40:42.567 --> 01:40:46.696
Sarah Winger knows God's love.

1214
01:40:51.284 --> 01:40:53.327
Come on, Son. Let's go.

1215
01:41:12.221 --> 01:41:14.265
Step down, Uncle Rob.

1216
01:41:14.348 --> 01:41:16.309
How far from the road?

1217
01:41:16.392 --> 01:41:17.852
Just a little ways.

1218
01:41:55.097 --> 01:41:57.433
What are you doin' with that gun, boy?
Come back here!


1219
01:41:58.559 --> 01:42:01.479
Maybe he's going after the Winger kid.
Call Kirky!


1220
01:42:03.356 --> 01:42:04.899
[bell ringing]

1221
01:42:18.204 --> 01:42:21.374
[train whistle blows]

1222
01:42:22.375 --> 01:42:26.128
Are you gonna like living up there in
the north with your sister Clara, Newt?


1223
01:42:26.921 --> 01:42:30.257
[Newt] I don't know.
I'm gonna miss my friends.


1224
01:42:30.341 --> 01:42:31.842
[Rob] Well, it's best for you.

1225
01:42:31.926 --> 01:42:34.679
Better schools and everything.

1226
01:42:34.762 --> 01:42:36.889
You got a chance up there.

1227
01:42:36.972 --> 01:42:39.141
That's what your mama
always wanted for you.


1228
01:42:40.518 --> 01:42:41.769
Yeah, I know.

1229
01:42:43.020 --> 01:42:47.233
Well, I'll talk to you
before you leave tomorrow.


1230
01:42:48.275 --> 01:42:49.694
Okay, Uncle Rob.

1231
01:42:57.159 --> 01:43:00.037
[train whistle blows]

1232
01:43:21.684 --> 01:43:23.144
Winger!

1233
01:43:35.823 --> 01:43:37.533
[hammer clicking]

1234
01:44:21.285 --> 01:44:24.079
[panting] I oughta kill you!

1235
01:44:28.626 --> 01:44:30.711
-But I can't.
-[motorcycle approaches]


1236
01:44:32.171 --> 01:44:34.673
Kirky will kill me. 
Let me up, let me up.

1237
01:44:35.591 --> 01:44:36.759
Let me up.

1238
01:44:51.899 --> 01:44:53.901
[engine stops]

1239
01:44:54.735 --> 01:44:56.403
Well, where's he at?

1240
01:44:57.321 --> 01:44:58.656
Where is he?

1241
01:44:58.739 --> 01:45:00.157
He went in the woods.

1242
01:45:18.926 --> 01:45:20.636
-[gunshot]
-[screams]


1243
01:45:30.563 --> 01:45:32.523
[sniffling]

1244
01:45:34.400 --> 01:45:36.819
Well, Winger, you can rest easy now.

1245
01:45:36.902 --> 01:45:38.821
Won't be botherin' with him no more.

1246
01:45:43.784 --> 01:45:45.286
[Newt sobs]

1247
01:45:54.837 --> 01:45:56.839
Aren't you gonna try to get him out?

1248
01:45:57.882 --> 01:46:00.175
No hurry about that.
He ain't goin' anywhere.


1249
01:46:02.344 --> 01:46:03.846
Cut deep?

1250
01:46:03.929 --> 01:46:05.306
It's okay.

1251
01:46:10.936 --> 01:46:13.147
Get on the back.
I'll give you a lift home.


1252
01:46:16.025 --> 01:46:17.693
| can make it by myself.

1253
01:46:20.446 --> 01:46:22.948
Okay by me... boy.

1254
01:46:26.493 --> 01:46:28.370
[engine starts]